Integration test suite for `ctx_brief::runner::run`, exercising the gather‚Üíplan pipeline end-to-end against in-memory fakes (`common::fake_fs`, `common::fake_claude`) instead of real subprocess/filesystem calls.

Covers: headless mode (two `print` calls ‚Äî grounded gather pass on `haiku` with a context-probe tool, then a tool-less plan pass fed the gather dossier), interactive mode (single seeded interactive call, success/failure depending on whether the session writes the brief file), missing-prompt error propagation (`BriefError::PromptMissing`), and request-resolution fallback (when `cfg`'s second arg doesn't match a backlog status row, the raw string is passed through verbatim as the gather user message).

Relies on `common::{cfg, fake_claude, fake_fs, seeded}` ‚Äî `seeded(bool)` builds a fake world with or without a populated backlog/status file; `cfg(headless: bool, request: &str)` builds a `Config`. `FakeClaude` records calls retrievable via `nth_print(i)` / `nth_interactive(i)`, each exposing `.system`, `.user`, `.model`, `.tools`, `.cwd`. Output path convention `.context/.reports/briefs/item.md` is asserted literally ‚Äî if `runner::run`'s output-path logic changes, these string literals must be updated in lockstep. `assert_headless_calls` returns `Option<()>` (not `Result`) purely so `?` can short-circuit inside a `#[test]` via `.expect(...)` at the call site.